---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Auspex"
  description="Auspex is the desktop-first operator shell for Omegon and Styrene."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">Preliminary site scaffold</div>
    <h1>Auspex is the operator shell for Omegon and Styrene.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This Astro site is intentionally minimal and not launched yet. It exists to establish
      repository structure, Cloudflare Pages build conventions, and a future place for product and
      documentation-facing content.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Desktop-first</h2>
      <p>Auspex is a Dioxus application focused on attached-session control, transport-aware routing, and operator telemetry.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>IPC-first embedded control</h2>
      <p>Embedded and local control paths prioritize IPC while remote and transitional attach paths still preserve websocket compatibility where needed.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Docs stay close to code</h2>
      <p>Long-lived design docs and OpenSpec changes remain in-repo so implementation, release policy, and architecture can drift less.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Not launched yet</h2>
    <p class="lede">
      Planned target host: <code>auspex.styrene.io</code>. This repository change scaffolds the site and Cloudflare Pages build metadata only; it does not create or deploy a Pages project.
    </p>
    <pre>cd site
npm install
npm run dev
npm run build</pre>
  </section>

  <footer>
    Auspex site scaffold — dormant until launch sequencing, content, and Cloudflare Pages project setup are intentionally approved.
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
